Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of reported cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 7 817 294, with reports of cases by 217 countries and territories worldwide. The global case count increased by 1.1% in the past 24 hours. The USA, with more than 2.13 million confirmed cases, now represents 27.3% of the global cases of COVID-19, as other countries such as Brazil, Chile, Peru, Mexico, India, and Pakistan are reporting increased numbers of new and cumulative cases significantly. A global total of 430 400 deaths have been reported, an increase of 2164 deaths in the past 24 hours. A reminder that in the absence of well-developed contact tracing activities with testing of asymptomatic and mildly ill contacts, there is major under-reporting of numbers of infections with the SARS-CoV-2 virus, possibly 1/10th to 1/20th in order of magnitude. There are also individuals who stay at home throughout their illness, sometimes, unfortunately, dying at home and who are never officially confirmed as infected with the SARS-CoV-2. These data are presented to provide relative indicators of the situations in each of the countries and comparisons between countries and regions of the world.

In descending rank order, the USA is number one for cumulative confirmed cases of COVID-19, followed by Brazil, Russia, India, the UK, Spain, Italy, Peru, Germany, and Iran at number 10. China is now number 19, changing this ordering in the past 24 hours. In descending rank order, the USA is number one for number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours, followed by India, Russia, Chile, Pakistan, Mexico, Saudi Arabia, Brazil, Bangladesh, and Iran; Peru and South Africa did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours, so the order in the top 10 list for number of newly confirmed cases is changed.

The top 20 countries in terms of absolute cumulative cases, which include 7 from the European region, 6 from the Americas region, 4 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 2 from the South East Asia region, and one from the Western Pacific region, unchanged in the past 120 hours. There are no countries from the Africa region. The top 20 countries with most newly confirmed cases include 8 from the Americas region, 5 from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 4 from the European region, 2 from the South-East Asia region, and one from the African region, none from the Western Pacific region. This listing very much reflects the "hot spots" in terms of countries with ongoing high transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 virus. - Mod.UBA]
